(42, 'Master of Applied Business Analytics', 'Technology Innovation Management', 'Technology Innovation Management (TIM) is a unique master’s program to train aspiring entrepreneurs on creating wealth at the early stages of company or opportunity life cycles. The program focuses on the launch and growth of technology companies and growth seeking initiatives of existing companies. The program provides benefits to founders of new companies, people seeking more senior leadership roles at existing companies, and talented professionals building credentials and expertise for their next career move. The program offers a number of hands-on opportunities.\r\n\r\nThe Master of Applied Business Analytics (MABA) is a pathway in the TIM program that targets individuals who want to specialize in the application of advanced business analytics to solve technology innovation management and technology entrepreneurship problems.', 1, 2, 19, '$13,213.00 CAD / Year', '2 Years', '4-Year Bachelor\'s Degree, Minimum GPA 73.0%,IELTS 6.5', '$26,685.00 CAD / Year', '$120.00 CAD', ',Jan 2024, Sep 2024', 'https://admin.edumatric.com/uploads/coursedocument/Pv44ZU3A8CVQzrPCRVLhrwbb8CNdPPiBt6naPB5y.png', '2023-05-22 18:00:00', '2024-02-28 18:00:00', '2023-09-05 00:32:00', '2023-09-07 00:34:43'),
(43, 'MSc in Biomedical Engineering and Biotechnology', 'Master of Science in Biomedical Engineering and Biotechnology', 'UMass Dartmouth distinguishes itself as a vibrant, public research university dedicated to engaged learning and innovative research resulting in personal and lifelong student success. The University serves as an intellectual catalyst for economic, social, and cultural transformation on a global, national, and regional scale.\r\n\r\nUMass Dartmouth will be a globally recognized premier research university committed to inclusion, access, advancement of knowledge, student success, and community engagement.\r\n\r\n\"The University of Massachusetts (UMass) is ranked #191 worldwide by Times Higher Education. UMass Dartmouth is a public research university, ranked #112 for top public schools among nationally ranked universities by U.S. News & World Report. UMass Dartmouth has been named the Best College for Business, Computer Science, and Nursing program by U.S. News & World Report. As a gem campus in the UMass system, we\'re only 15 minutes from the beach, 1 hour south of Boston and 3 hours from New York City.\r\nUMass Dartmouth offers more than 40 undergraduate STEM programs among 100+ academic programs, 40 masters, and 12 doctoral programs. Our graduates are employed by companies such as Google, Johnson & Johnson, Dreamworks, and Siemens and continue their education at prestigious institutions, including Harvard Medical School, MIT, Brown University, and the University of Michigan. Undergraduate applicants with a 2.75 GPA and above can receive a $10,000-$15,500 scholarship per academic year for four years. With the up to 50% tuition discount, students can also sign up for an 8 or 10-monthly payment plan with international currency and work on campus to earn $15+ per hour. \"', 2, 2, 20, '$1600 per year', '2 Years', '4 Years Bachelor\'s Degree CGPA at least 3, IELTS 6', '29,578 per year', '$60', '2024-01-22', 'https://admin.edumatric.com/uploads/coursedocument/m52ody7KK60pui29PHhe88GwWsITwTo82ssYLmhT.jpg', '2023-01-22 18:00:00', '2024-01-16 18:00:00', '2023-09-05 00:52:29', '2023-09-07 00:43:45'),
(44, 'Master of Actuarial Science', 'Actuarial Science', 'Actuarial science includes a number of interrelated subjects, including probability, mathematics, statistics, finance, economics, and mathematics of finance. The Master of Actuarial Science will prepare students for the professional exams necessary to become an Actuary in North America with accreditation accepted in many other parts of the world. They will study and live in Canada for approximately 16 months (4 academic terms) while enrolled in a total of 12 courses. The courses will include actuarial mathematics as required for the Society of Actuaries (SOA) professional exams. As a professional graduate program, alumni of the M.Act.Sc program are well prepared for careers in insurance, pensions, and healthcare industries. Graduates can also participate in one of the regular offerings of the Society of Actuaries (SOA) exams offered on-site.', 1, 2, 21, '$13,210.00 CAD / Year', '16 month masters Degree', '3-Year Bachelor\'s Degree, Minimum GPA 70.0%,IELTS 6.5', '$34,000.00 CAD / Year', '$125.00 CAD', 'Likely Open', 'https://admin.edumatric.com/uploads/coursedocument/avPscJrtkcj5WuQLV372reOAPZDK2isbzmtYu3xa.png', '2023-09-02 18:00:00', '2023-09-02 18:00:00', '2023-09-05 00:52:50', '2023-09-07 00:44:58'),
(45, 'Master of Applied Computing', 'Applied Computing', 'The Master of Applied Computing is a course-based professional graduate program offered by the School of Computer Science will provide students with a solid foundation and knowledge of industry oriented practical aspects of Computer Science, preparing them to take up positions in the growing software industry in Canada and around the world.\r\n\r\nThe skills and knowledge gained from this program will allow students to develop a successful career in the growing software industry through practical projects, internships and in-class training. This program has been specifically designed to expose them to the latest technologies and developments in a number of high-demand fields.', 1, 2, 21, '$13,210.00 CAD / Year', '16 month masters Degree', '4-Year Bachelor\'s Degree, Minimum GPA 70.0%,IELTS 6.5', '$28,500.00 CAD / Year', '$125.00 CAD', 'Likely Open', 'https://admin.edumatric.com/uploads/coursedocument/22QtsiGoJbr3a0j93LsA3qpqjRTRYMgRBurGOclr.png', '2023-09-02 18:00:00', '2023-09-02 18:00:00', '2023-09-05 00:55:03', '2023-09-07 00:45:47'),
(46, 'Master of Applied Economics and Policy', 'Applied Economics and Policy', 'The Master of Applied Economics and Policy program is designed to offer a unique combination of courses that will prepare students for work in the specialized field of economic policy. As a graduate, students will be prepared to immediately secure a position in the working world. The program places special emphasis in preparing students to utilize large amounts of data available to professionals in government and business to improve the efficiency and effectiveness of government polices and business projects. Through a multidisciplinary approach to policy analysis involving economic courses, business courses, communication workshops and an exciting research project, students will have all of the tools and experiences needed to begin a career as an Economist.', 1, 2, 21, '$13,210.00 CAD / Year', '16 month masters Degree', '3-Year Bachelor\'s Degree, Minimum GPA 70.0%,IELTS 6.5', '$25,988.00 CAD / Year', '$125.00 CAD', 'Likely Open', 'https://admin.edumatric.com/uploads/coursedocument/75VQONTtScHgxWnwE998KORSpkkWPVLaqAgFpGSq.png', '2023-09-03 18:00:00', '2023-09-03 18:00:00', '2023-09-05 00:58:48', '2023-09-07 00:44:09'),
(47, 'MBA', 'Master of Business Administration', 'This Odette Master of Business Administration (MBA) is an intensive program with an integrated curriculum combining lectures, case studies, computer simulations, and real-world client presentations to prepare students for success in the business world. This program is designed to give them a solid grounding in the fundamental areas of commerce, as well as providing up-to-date coverage of the latest business advances. With an Odette MBA, students will enjoy a higher return on their educational investment and reap greater career dividends.', 1, 2, 21, '$13,210.00 CAD / Year', '16 month masters Degree', '3-Year Bachelor\'s Degree, Minimum GPA 70.0%,IELTS 7', '$33,300.00 CAD / Year', '$125.00 CAD', 'Likely Open', 'https://admin.edumatric.com/uploads/coursedocument/y2fXqIRQFDSmL846vGXGjQsuoU4l2lOGFNANCagD.png', '2023-09-03 18:00:00', '2023-09-03 18:00:00', '2023-09-05 01:00:48', '2023-09-07 00:46:56'),
(48, 'MSc in Mechanical Engineering', 'Master of Science in Mechanical Engineering', 'Founded in 1889 as New Mexico’s flagship institution, The University of New Mexico now occupies nearly 800 acres near old Route 66 in the heart of Albuquerque, a metropolitan area of more than 900,000 people. From the magnificent mesas to the west, past the banks of the historic Rio Grande to the Sandia Mountains to the east, Albuquerque is a blend of culture and cuisine, styles and stories, people, pursuits and panoramas.\r\nOffering a distinctive campus environment with a Pueblo Revival architectural theme, the campus buildings echo nearby Pueblo Indian villages. The nationally recognized campus arboretum and the popular duck pond offer an outstanding botanical experience in the midst of one of New Mexico\'s great public open spaces.', 2, 2, 13, '$13704 per year', '2 Years', '4 Years Bachelor\'s Degree CGPA at least 3, IELTS 6.5', '27,846 per year', '$70', '2024-01-15', 'https://admin.edumatric.com/uploads/coursedocument/7MkSqVMmBatqwBGyoaf26vJuAAgeBAe5ZTuMbWsj.jpg', '2023-01-15 18:00:00', '2023-07-31 18:00:00', '2023-09-05 01:02:15', '2023-09-07 00:25:57'),
(49, 'Master of Engineering', 'Civil Engineering (Optional Co-op)', 'The Department of Civil and Environmental Engineering graduate programs create and maintain excellence in areas at the forefront of research and innovation. Its objective is to attract the best students and to educate them in the rigours of scientific research. It provides a scholarly and dynamic environment with attention to scientific discipline, detail and accuracy.\r\n\r\nThe Master of Engineering is a course-based program designed for working professionals or recent graduates who want to increase their knowledge in multiple, advanced topics. Graduates of the MEng program can apply to University of Windsor\'s fast-track MASc program, which provides them with additional research-specific training and education. MEng students will be required to complete a minimum of eight graduate-level courses, including five from their area of specialization plus three required courses: Engineering Technical Communications, Engineering Mathematics and Engineering Project Management. Full-time students must complete this program in 3-5 semesters.', 1, 2, 21, '$13,210.00 CAD / Year', '2 Years', '3-Year Bachelor\'s Degree, Minimum GPA 72.0%,IELTS 7', '$28,800.00 CAD / Year', '$125.00 CAD', 'May 2024', 'https://admin.edumatric.com/uploads/coursedocument/eGzYzCj9PrCqJ0MjtoOxczwBqZTGBut039b6fObF.png', '2023-05-10 18:00:00', '2023-09-03 18:00:00', '2023-09-05 01:03:07', '2023-09-07 00:47:40'),
(50, 'MSc in Software Engineering', 'Master of Science in Software Engineering', 'We are the University of Houston-Clear Lake, and we have been opening doors for accessible education since 1974. As part of the University of Houston System, we offer more than 90 graduate and undergraduate programs online or face-to-face at locations in Clear Lake, Pearland and the Texas Medical Center.\r\n\r\nAcross our four colleges — the College of Business, College of Education, College of Human Sciences and Humanities, and College of Science and Engineering — student experiences inside and outside of the classroom demonstrate our impact beyond the campus. With more than 100 student organizations and various campus traditions, you have plenty of opportunities to get involved and form new friendships. As a student at the University of Houston-Clear Lake, you\'ll experience:\r\nReal connections with faculty members who are experts in their fields.\r\nA valuable education that is recognized by leading national accrediting agencies in education, social work, sciences and more.\r\nBeautiful, safe campus on 524 acres of natural green space. Entertainment, sports and arts within a half-hour drive.\r\nGlobal influences through a diverse community of students, faculty, staff and alumni.', 2, 2, 22, '$12000 Per Year', '2 Years', '4 Years Bachelor\'s Degree CGPA at least 3, IELTS 6', '19,082 per year', '$75', '2024-01-15', 'https://admin.edumatric.com/uploads/coursedocument/tOKE9COGgUvWpagcfNuYWCWh9jA58dic0Zr1gSEU.jpg', '2023-01-13 18:00:00', '2023-09-29 18:00:00', '2023-09-05 01:10:29', '2023-09-07 01:17:32'),
(51, 'Graduate Diploma', 'Environmental Public Health Practice', 'This 1-year Graduate Diploma in Environmental Public Health Practice is intended to provide students with comprehensive knowledge and skills required to function competently as professionals in the Environmental Health field. This program explores all aspects of the natural and built environment that can influence human health and disease.\r\n\r\nExplore the diversity of the field with topics including:\r\n\r\nFood and drinking water safety\r\nWaste management\r\nAir and soil quality\r\ncommunicable diseases\r\nEmergency response\r\nOccupational Health\r\nConcordia University of Edmonton’s Environmental Public Health Practice Diploma allows students to enter careers in the food safety sector, government, private industry, as well as provide comprehensive public health knowledge to advance in their current place of employment.', 1, 2, 23, '$11,000.00 CAD / Year', '16 month graduate diploma', '3-Year Bachelor\'s Degree, Minimum GPA 73.0%,IELTS 6', '$18,529.00 CAD / Year', '$100.00 CAD', 'Sep 2024', 'https://admin.edumatric.com/uploads/coursedocument/07a58i5gWGtxQx9xw2miYQJwMEEx4fXh4EAqsqUs.png', '2023-10-01 18:00:00', '2024-09-29 18:00:00', '2023-09-05 01:10:42', '2023-09-07 00:59:08'),
(52, 'Master of Information Systems', 'Assurance Management', 'The need for information systems and security professionals is growing along with increasing reliance of businesses and governments on the technology. The demand for information systems security and assurance professionals shows no end in sight. This program maintains a sharp focus on the needs of employers and changes in industry. The Assurance program focuses on the business aspect of IT and prospective candidates are expected to have a background in both technology and accounting/finance.\r\n\r\nThis program follows the Information Systems Audit and Control Association (ISACA) model curriculum and follow ISACA best practices and normally encourage students to pursue a COBIT 2019 Foundation certification during the program and some consider other COBIT 2019 certifications and other ISACA certifications.', 1, 2, 23, '$11,000.00 CAD / Year', '2 Years', '4-Year Bachelor\'s Degree, Minimum GPA 73.0%,IELTS 6', '$24,144.00 CAD / Year', '$100.00 CAD', 'Sep 2024', 'https://admin.edumatric.com/uploads/coursedocument/n9o6sSe5OcWqOY93GuXCkCelaB4crgpupAOWM3cS.png', '2023-09-03 18:00:00', '2024-03-30 18:00:00', '2023-09-05 01:13:27', '2023-09-07 01:00:26'),
(53, 'MSc in Nanoscience and Microsystems Engineering', 'Master of Science in Nanoscience and Microsystems Engineering', 'Founded in 1889 as New Mexico’s flagship institution, The University of New Mexico now occupies nearly 800 acres near old Route 66 in the heart of Albuquerque, a metropolitan area of more than 900,000 people. From the magnificent mesas to the west, past the banks of the historic Rio Grande to the Sandia Mountains to the east, Albuquerque is a blend of culture and cuisine, styles and stories, people, pursuits and panoramas. Offering a distinctive campus environment with a Pueblo Revival architectural theme, the campus buildings echo nearby Pueblo Indian villages. The nationally recognized campus arboretum and the popular duck pond offer an outstanding botanical experience in the midst of one of New Mexico\'s great public open spaces.', 2, 2, 13, '$13704 per year', '2 Years', '4 Years Bachelor\'s Degree CGPA at least 3, IELTS 6.5', '27,846 per year', '$70', '2024-01-15', 'https://admin.edumatric.com/uploads/coursedocument/MLUwfcfA5sdz2p7Ltt9ydCLG8Ux0v1LOTpKIbe8M.png', '2023-01-15 18:00:00', '2023-07-31 18:00:00', '2023-09-05 01:16:09', '2023-09-07 03:09:16'),
(54, 'Master of Information Systems', 'Security Management', 'Concordia University of Edmonton is proud to bring students a unique, mature and much-needed Information Systems Security program.\r\n\r\nThe need for security professionals is growing along with increasing reliance of businesses and governments on IT. The employer demand for information systems security professionals shows no end in sight. The program maintains a sharp focus on the needs of employers and changes in industry.\r\n\r\nThe program allows students preparation time for writing the certification exam for Certified Information Systems Security Professional (CISSP). Some students/graduates also choose to write the certification exam for Certified Information Security Manager (CISM) as well as Certified Information Systems Auditor (CISA).', 1, 2, 23, '$11,000.00 CAD / Year', '20 month master\'s degree', '4-Year Bachelor\'s Degree, Minimum GPA 73.0%,IELTS 6', '$27,203.00 CAD / Year', '$100.00 CAD', 'Sep 2024', 'https://admin.edumatric.com/uploads/coursedocument/mTR9qq0hZAnP4zwszqRzmLDuEBJByH4FSJfikrz6.png', '2023-09-03 18:00:00', '2024-03-30 18:00:00', '2023-09-05 01:16:26', '2023-09-07 01:01:19'),
(55, 'Graduate Diploma', 'Information Assurance', 'The Graduate Diploma in Information Assurance is a credit coursework program. Any coursework completed or graduate diploma received will count towards the Master of Information Systems Assurance Management (MISAM) program should students apply to the MISAM program and get accepted.\r\n\r\nAs MISSM graduates, students may not apply for the MISAM degree; however, they may apply for and receive the Graduate Diploma in Information Assurance if they wish to broaden their assurance, information systems audit and governance knowledge.', 1, 2, 23, '$11,000.00 CAD / Year', '1 Year graduate diploma', '3-Year Bachelor\'s Degree, Minimum GPA 77.0%,IELTS 6.5', '$18,180.00 CAD / Year', '$100.00 CAD', 'Sep 2024', 'https://admin.edumatric.com/uploads/coursedocument/9jFtNZANnYEx39xpBSIqj3Wttj0ZQQaqO5edRJlc.png', '2023-09-03 18:00:00', '2024-03-30 18:00:00', '2023-09-05 01:19:50', '2023-09-07 01:03:30'),
(56, 'Graduate Diploma', 'Information Security', 'The Graduate Diploma in Information Security is an 18-credit program and is entirely coursework. Any coursework completed or diploma received will count towards the Master of Information Systems Security Management (MISSM) degree should students decide to apply to the MISSM program and get accepted.\r\n\r\nStudents who are a Master of Information Systems Security Management degree graduate, they may not apply for the Master of Information Systems Security Management degree, however they may receive the Graduate Diploma in Information Security.', 1, 2, 23, '$11,000.00 CAD / Year', '1 Year graduate diploma', '4-Year Bachelor\'s Degree, Minimum GPA 73.0%,IELTS 6', '$24,654.00 CAD / Year', '$100.00 CAD', 'Sep 2024', 'https://admin.edumatric.com/uploads/coursedocument/mqQozeOiUSjBPJba0IkdPbsl310oSguFSlwNiYKl.png', '2023-09-03 18:00:00', '2024-03-30 18:00:00', '2023-09-05 01:22:02', '2023-09-07 01:04:10'),
(57, 'Master of Business Administration', 'International Business', 'The Master of Business Administration (MBA) develops innovative, entrepreneurial leaders through small class sizes, a diverse international student body and access to faculty members who are leaders in their field — in one year.\r\n\r\nNo matter the area of specialization, students gain access to networking opportunities, business consulting projects and the chance to round out their education abroad.\r\n\r\nStudents in the International Business program at UNB will make the leap from textbook to hands-on international business management overseas. This is the experiential education students need to compete globally.', 1, 2, 24, '$10,000.00 CAD / Year', '15 month master\'s degree including practicum', '4-Year Bachelor\'s Degree, Minimum GPA 75.0%,IELTS 7', '$29,505.00 CAD / Year', '$125.00 CAD', 'Sep 2024', 'https://admin.edumatric.com/uploads/coursedocument/HOtqeBUCjZIRfgH9PMI5W9YGgvMB7aIicHWE7SJ4.png', '2023-07-02 18:00:00', '2023-09-03 18:00:00', '2023-09-05 01:26:50', '2023-09-07 01:11:11'),
(58, 'MBA', 'Entrepreneurship and Technology Management', 'The Master of Business Administration (MBA) develops innovative, entrepreneurial leaders through small class sizes, a diverse international student body and access to faculty members who are leaders in their field — in one year.\r\n\r\nNo matter the area of specialization, students will gain access to networking opportunities, business consulting projects and the chance to round out their education abroad.\r\n\r\nAn MBA in Entrepreneurship and Technology Management is challenging and fast-paced – designed to shape future business leaders.\r\n\r\nThis program —one of five available as part of the Faculty of Business’s Master of Business Administration — will equip students for the real world. Thanks to the small class sizes, students will graduate with the experience and skills necessary to manage innovation in a dynamic environment.\r\n\r\nStudents will foster creativity and practicality as they go through the process of creating a new product or service, and discover a modern approach to bring it to the marketplace.', 1, 2, 24, '$10,000.00 CAD / Year', '1 year master\'s degree including an internship', '4-Year Bachelor\'s Degree, Minimum GPA 75.0%,IELTS 7', '$29,505.00 CAD / Year', '$125.00 CAD', 'Sep 2024', 'https://admin.edumatric.com/uploads/coursedocument/uyPUc7pyt37UexA7FyUIcOKzr2SCZ5mUF25F9BfU.png', '2023-07-02 18:00:00', '2023-09-03 18:00:00', '2023-09-05 01:29:57', '2023-09-07 01:12:02'),
(59, 'Master of Business Administration (MBA)', 'General Management', 'The Master of Business Administration (MBA) develops innovative, entrepreneurial leaders through small class sizes, a diverse international student body and access to faculty members who are leaders in their field — in one year.\r\n\r\nNo matter the area of specialization, students will gain access to networking opportunities, business consulting projects and the chance to round out their education abroad.\r\n\r\nA challenging learning environment has been created to give students a strong business foundation from which to launch their career. Develop managerial potential in areas relevant to the modern economy while learning from and collaborating with students from around the world, who bring their own perspectives and experience.', 1, 2, 24, '$10,000.00 CAD / Year', '1 year master\'s degree', '4-Year Bachelor\'s Degree, Minimum GPA 75.0%,IELTS 7', '$29,505.00 CAD / Year', '$125.00 CAD', 'Sep 2024', 'https://admin.edumatric.com/uploads/coursedocument/V6VGG4SfJLhs6QBZkZdwJ0lPKFatmL9Ha2mkvqGn.png', '2023-07-02 18:00:00', '2024-07-30 18:00:00', '2023-09-05 01:33:12', '2023-09-07 01:12:37'),
(60, 'Master of Business Administration', 'Project Management', 'At UNB Saint John, students learn the methodology and best practices of project management from subject-matter experts. UNB\'s students graduate with the tools and techniques necessary for effective leadership and excellent communication.\r\n\r\nProject management is one of the fastest growing areas of employment in North America – a great next step for students with backgrounds in engineering, operations and technology.\r\n\r\nThis specialization is one of five available in the Faculty of Business’s Master of Business Administration program.', 1, 2, 24, '$10,000.00 CAD / Year', '1 year master\'s degree', '4-Year Bachelor\'s Degree, Minimum GPA 75.0%,IELTS 7', '$29,505.00 CAD / Year', '$125.00 CAD', 'Sep 2024', 'https://admin.edumatric.com/uploads/coursedocument/6KRAosSfYGgKGWYGaLDLS5rBLbYaVXX3IqidDbX3.png', '2023-07-02 18:00:00', '2023-09-03 18:00:00', '2023-09-05 01:35:08', '2023-09-07 01:13:23'),
(61, 'Master of Business Administration', 'Business Development and Professional Sales', 'UNB Saint John is proud to offer Canada’s first business development and sales specialization as part of its one-year intensive MBA Program.\r\n\r\nThe program is designed to create business development and sales professionals who are competing and winning in an environment where business development is fueled by professional sales. \r\n\r\nStudents will take their career to the next level with courses in the art of negotiation, the value of data analytics and the science of decision-making.\r\n\r\nThe negotiation courses will equip students to understand the causes and consequences of conflict, explore methods of reducing the occurrence of conflict, examine conflict resolution models, and understand and apply negotiation and dispute resolution principles.\r\n\r\nThe data analytics course will provide students with the foundational knowledge of analytics and data-driven decision-making, empowering professionals from C-suite executives to front-line salespeople to solve problems and make strategic decisions.\r\n\r\nStudents will also take a deep dive into behavioural economics to understand how consumers make decisions and how to manage interactions through the decision-making process.\r\n\r\nFull time students will also have the opportunity to gain hands on experience by working with a company or organization on a business consulting project as part of their program.', 1, 2, 24, '$10,000.00 CAD / Year', '1 year master\'s degree', '4-Year Bachelor\'s Degree, Minimum GPA 75.0%,IELTS 7', '$29,505.00 CAD / Year', '$125.00 CAD', 'Sep 2024', 'https://admin.edumatric.com/uploads/coursedocument/9NnMfymLlNQWR500EkVhoxyBHq6u8GpdIBhlgl5c.png', '2023-07-02 18:00:00', '2023-09-03 18:00:00', '2023-09-05 01:37:04', '2023-09-07 01:14:24'),
(62, 'MSc in Nanoscience and Microsystems Engineering', 'Master of Science in Nanoscience and Microsystems Engineering', 'Founded in 1889 as New Mexico’s flagship institution, The University of New Mexico now occupies nearly 800 acres near old Route 66 in the heart of Albuquerque, a metropolitan area of more than 900,000 people. From the magnificent mesas to the west, past the banks of the historic Rio Grande to the Sandia Mountains to the east, Albuquerque is a blend of culture and cuisine, styles and stories, people, pursuits and panoramas.\r\n\r\nOffering a distinctive campus environment with a Pueblo Revival architectural theme, the campus buildings echo nearby Pueblo Indian villages. The nationally recognized campus arboretum and the popular duck pond offer an outstanding botanical experience in the midst of one of New Mexico\'s great public open spaces.', 2, 2, 13, '16000', '2 Years', '4 Years Bachelor\'s Degree CGPA at least 3, IELTS 6.5', '27,846 per year', '70 USD', '2024-01-15', 'https://admin.edumatric.com/uploads/coursedocument/jWYBULrCCvy4P2m6OIUL5QfT7yZUhn4GItLxZADc.png', '2023-01-15 18:00:00', '2023-02-18 18:00:00', '2023-09-05 01:41:57', '2023-09-07 00:54:41'),
(63, 'MSc in Manufacturing Engineering', 'Master of Engineering in Manufacturing Engineering', 'Founded in 1889 as New Mexico’s flagship institution, The University of New Mexico now occupies nearly 800 acres near old Route 66 in the heart of Albuquerque, a metropolitan area of more than 900,000 people. From the magnificent mesas to the west, past the banks of the historic Rio Grande to the Sandia Mountains to the east, Albuquerque is a blend of culture and cuisine, styles and stories, people, pursuits and panoramas.\r\n\r\nOffering a distinctive campus environment with a Pueblo Revival architectural theme, the campus buildings echo nearby Pueblo Indian villages. The nationally recognized campus arboretum and the popular duck pond offer an outstanding botanical experience in the midst of one of New Mexico\'s great public open spaces.', 2, 2, 13, '$13000 per year', '2 Years', '4 Years Bachelor\'s Degree CGPA at least 3, IELTS 6.5', '27,846 per year', '$70', '2024-01-15', 'https://admin.edumatric.com/uploads/coursedocument/eb1Zw1NSdJ6rQ9rLfRiIH80NV1A7gLgCOLlvDWDr.png', '2023-01-15 18:00:00', '2023-02-18 18:00:00', '2023-09-05 02:12:46', '2023-09-07 03:18:11'),
(64, 'MSc in Civil Engineering', 'Master of Science in Civil Engineering', 'Founded in 1889 as New Mexico’s flagship institution, The University of New Mexico now occupies nearly 800 acres near old Route 66 in the heart of Albuquerque, a metropolitan area of more than 900,000 people. From the magnificent mesas to the west, past the banks of the historic Rio Grande to the Sandia Mountains to the east, Albuquerque is a blend of culture and cuisine, styles and stories, people, pursuits and panoramas.\r\n\r\nOffering a distinctive campus environment with a Pueblo Revival architectural theme, the campus buildings echo nearby Pueblo Indian villages. The nationally recognized campus arboretum and the popular duck pond offer an outstanding botanical experience in the midst of one of New Mexico\'s great public open spaces.', 2, 2, 13, '$13000 per year', '2 Years', '4 Years Bachelor\'s Degree CGPA at least 3, IELTS 6.5', '27,846 per year', '$70', '2024-01-15', 'https://admin.edumatric.com/uploads/coursedocument/rtOpaaL5r9SeRI3cXzoY2tQCvLQxaN6hkupnE1Ry.png', '2023-01-15 18:00:00', '2023-02-18 18:00:00', '2023-09-05 02:17:38', '2023-09-07 01:20:03'),
(65, 'Bachelor of Science', 'Science and Business', 'Students will be able to jumpstart their career with a one-of-a-kind degree that equips them with both scientific know-how and valuable business skills. Science and Business at the University of Waterloo combines studies in biology, chemistry, and physics with courses in economics, accounting, marketing, law, and entrepreneurship.', 1, 1, 3, '$13,213.00 CAD / Year', '4-Year Bachelor\'s Degree', 'Grade 12 / High School, Minimum GPA 85%, IELTS 6.5', '$44,556.00 CAD / Year', '$251.00 CAD', 'Sep 2024', 'https://admin.edumatric.com/uploads/coursedocument/noYONa5k43KEGs6KH3Aq3tPdtYeFLJ8zbzxxmU4P.webp', '2023-09-03 18:00:00', '2024-01-30 18:00:00', '2023-09-05 03:45:40', '2023-09-05 04:31:32'),
(66, 'Bachelor of BGBDA', 'Bachelor of Global Business and Digital Arts (BGBDA)', 'In this unique program, students will spend their first year at the University of Waterloo\'s main campus, where students will gain a solid foundation linking creative design, globalization, business ethics, economics, and marketing.\r\n\r\nFor final three years, students will move to the University of Waterloo\'s Stratford School of Interaction Design and Business, located 45 kilometres west of the main campus. There, students will develop design-driven solutions to social problems and create new forms of cultural expressions in a global context. And thanks to the University of Waterloo\'s  project-based approach, students will also hone their collaboration and project management skills.', 1, 1, 3, '$13,213.00 CAD / Year', '4-Year Bachelor\'s Degree', 'Grade 12 / High School, Minimum GPA 85%, IELTS 6.5', '$42,520.00 CAD / Year', '$251.00 CAD', 'Sep 2024', 'https://admin.edumatric.com/uploads/coursedocument/uCrlsygegdPLNMB4iGqKMyRCmAUwcz83hQvEO0zO.webp', '2023-09-03 18:00:00', '2024-01-30 18:00:00', '2023-09-05 03:47:13', '2023-09-05 03:51:16'),
(67, 'Bachelor of Science', 'Science and Business', 'Students will be able to jumpstart their career with a one-of-a-kind degree that equips them with both scientific know-how and valuable business skills. Science and Business at the University of Waterloo combines studies in biology, chemistry, and physics with courses in economics, accounting, marketing, law, and entrepreneurship.\r\n\r\nStudents will be able to focus their degree by specializing in one of three scientific disciplines, or take a broader range of courses tailored to their interests by remaining unspecialized. Meanwhile, in one of Canada’s top universities for business, students will work in small groups on case studies, business plans, and market analysis, as well as have the opportunity to gain paid work experience through the co-op stream.\r\n\r\nWhen students graduate, the opportunities are many: this is a degree students can put to work in intellectual property, research, mutual funds, technical sales, business development, law, and a host of other fields.', 1, 1, 3, '$13,213.00 CAD / Year', '4  year bachelor\'s degree', 'Grade 12 / High School, 85.0%, IELTS 6.5', '$44,556.00 CAD / Year', '$251.00 CAD', 'Sept 2024', 'https://admin.edumatric.com/uploads/coursedocument/VD4tVuH4Esmm7qvOdUzsNEkO4iHtMVfJ6LXNb0kC.png', '2024-04-29 18:00:00', '2024-05-30 18:00:00', '2023-09-05 22:25:52', '2023-09-07 02:44:34'),
(68, 'Bachelor of Mathematics', 'Business Administration', 'Technology is rapidly changing business, so demand for technically advanced individuals is at an all-time high. Students can earn a Bachelor of Mathematics by taking courses from two prestigious institutions-math courses from the University of Waterloo\'s Faculty of Mathematics and business courses from Wilfrid Laurier University\'s School of Business and Economics. Students who want more advanced quantitative and technical skills than are available through traditional business programs, then this program is designed for them..\r\n\r\nWhen students graduate, they will have all the skills they need for a career as an analyst, information specialist, trader, or many other options, along with paid work experience if students choose to enroll in the co-op stream.', 1, 1, 3, '$13,213.00 CAD / Year', '4  year bachelor\'s degree', 'Grade 12 / High School, Minimum GPA 90.0%, IELTS 6.5', '$46,034.00 CAD / Year', '$251.00 CAD', 'Sept 2024', 'https://admin.edumatric.com/uploads/coursedocument/r5xVdfRHkw28KgqtglOy5mxFlwhvD7wIK3EDvSVi.png', '2024-04-29 18:00:00', '2024-05-30 18:00:00', '2023-09-05 22:28:50', '2023-09-10 04:03:52'),
(69, 'Bachelor of Mathematics', 'Business Administration', 'Technology is rapidly changing business, so demand for technically advanced individuals is at an all-time high. Students can earn a Bachelor of Mathematics by taking courses from two prestigious institutions-math courses from the University of Waterloo\'s Faculty of Mathematics and business courses from Wilfrid Laurier University\'s School of Business and Economics. Students who want more advanced quantitative and technical skills than are available through traditional business programs, then this program is designed for them..\r\n\r\nWhen students graduate, they will have all the skills they need for a career as an analyst, information specialist, trader, or many other options, along with paid work experience if students choose to enroll in the co-op stream.', 1, 1, 3, '$13,213.00 CAD / Year', '4  year bachelor\'s degree', 'Grade 12 / High School, Minimum GPA 90.0%, IELTS 6.5', '$46,034.00 CAD / Year', '$251.00 CAD', 'Sept 2024', 'https://admin.edumatric.com/uploads/coursedocument/wvAEHHRo9FdY0BH7JxBGSp6pXwTHq9JCfpJ0QpKE.png', '2024-04-30 18:00:00', '2024-05-31 18:00:00', '2023-09-05 22:31:12', '2023-09-05 22:31:12'),
(70, 'Bachelor of Computer Science', 'Computer Science', 'Students will have an opportunity to study at one of the world’s best schools for computer science. Students will develop a broad understanding in areas such as systems and networks, algorithms, and programming. \r\n\r\nAfter first year, students can choose a major in Data Science. Students can also gain two years of paid work experience through the co-op program, the largest of its kind in North America, or fast track their degree by choosing the regular system of study.\r\n\r\nThe University of Waterloo’s graduates goes on to work in leading technology companies and at top universities around the world. Meanwhile, the University of Waterloo’s professors and graduates have created more than 800 spin-off companies, including leaders like OpenText, Canada’s largest software company.', 1, 1, 3, '$13,213.00 CAD / Year', '4  year bachelor\'s degree', 'Grade 12 / High School, Minimum GPA 95.0%, IELTS 6.5', '$63,350.00 CAD / Year', '$251.00 CAD', 'Sept 2024', 'https://admin.edumatric.com/uploads/coursedocument/LNn4ePbqvAKCxmMGO6nUoHf0u367loK8gizZBjqt.png', '2024-04-29 18:00:00', '2024-05-30 18:00:00', '2023-09-05 22:33:48', '2023-09-10 04:04:17'),
(71, 'Bachelor of Accounting and Financial Management (Co-op)', 'Accounting and Financial Management', 'Disruptive technologies are revolutionizing business. To compete, it\'s not enough to have a foundation in accounting and finance. Students also need a broad understanding of technology, business analytics, sustainability, and innovation.\r\n\r\nThat\'s why Students will study at the intersections of accounting, finance, and business while immersing themselves in diverse topics that give students the flexibility to design their unique pathway. Dive into collaborative, problem-based courses, then apply student’s learning to the real world through co-op work terms and co- and extra-curricular experiences. By cultivating an entrepreneurial mindset and leading-edge financial expertise, students will be ready to positively impact global economies with new perspectives and solutions.\r\n\r\nThe University of Waterloo’s School of Accounting and Finance has received the highest level of national accreditation through CPA Canada, as well as accreditation through the CFA Institute University Affiliation Program.', 1, 1, 3, '$13,213.00 CAD / Year', '4  year bachelor\'s degree', 'Grade 12 / High School, Minimum GPA 88.0%, IELTS 6.5', '$49,110.00 CAD / Year', '$251.00 CAD', 'Sept 2024', 'https://admin.edumatric.com/uploads/coursedocument/0bIAukq4mOk6mYj2hTOTCLfdrbQD8YdVFuSjFD5I.png', '2024-04-29 18:00:00', '2024-05-30 18:00:00', '2023-09-05 22:35:58', '2023-09-10 04:04:36'),
(72, 'Double Degree - Bachelor of Applied Science - Chemical Engineering & Bachelor of Science - Computing Technology (OEA) (Optional Co-op)', 'Chemical Engineering & Bachelor of Science', 'Chemical engineering is at the intersection of many disciplines, linking knowledge of basic and applied sciences, economics, and health and safety. Chemical engineering graduates use a series of operations to sustainably process raw natural materials into finished products. They work in any number of industries, and during their careers, they may face a variety of challenges, including optimizing processes, monitoring pollution, converting renewable energy, processing foods and drugs, and manufacturing new materials.\r\n\r\nThis double degree program combines a Bachelor of Applied Science with the Bachelor of Science in Computing Technology.', 1, 1, 4, '$13,213.00 CAD / Year', NULL, 'Grade 12 / High School, Minimum GPA 80.0%, IELTS 6.5', '$52,708.00 CAD / Year', '$256.00 CAD', 'Sept 2024', 'https://admin.edumatric.com/uploads/coursedocument/q2vMydSQKw5qZGWCOBa0W6XGE2hMYIJMEp0YuqoT.png', '2024-04-29 18:00:00', '2024-05-30 18:00:00', '2023-09-05 22:43:45', '2023-09-10 04:07:58'),
(73, 'MBA', 'Master of Business Administration', 'Interested applicants can further their career through the Master of Business Administration at the University of New Brunswick in Fredericton.\r\n\r\nUNB\'s unique and highly professional program will hone a student\'s leadership skills and give them the tools to make effective decisions within a dynamic and ever-changing business environment.\r\n\r\nStudents can tailor the program directly to their field of work, whether that’s accounting, quant, finance or entrepreneurship.\r\n\r\nUNB\'s MBA program is 20 months — or four semesters — and consists of 18 courses. The first year builds a solid foundation within business by taking 10 required courses. In second year students will choose six elective courses and focus on their area(s) of interest through coursework, coursework and project, or coursework and thesis.\r\n\r\nStudents will also develop a capstone project in their final year and work with real companies to develop and pitch a competitive strategic plan.\r\n\r\n*The Faculty of Management at the University of New Brunswick Fredericton is AACSB Accredited. AACSB accreditation is known worldwide as the longest-standing, most recognized form of specialized accreditation that an institution and its business programs can earn.', 1, 2, 25, '$10,000.00 CAD / Year', '20 month master\'s degree', '4-Year Bachelor\'s Degree, Minimum GPA 73.0%,IELTS 7', '$19,450.00 CAD / Year', '$125.00 CAD', 'Sep 2024', 'https://admin.edumatric.com/uploads/coursedocument/BiHsUmaXMVAixfCvCbal2LVFTLc8oUVIJHP5WKRR.png', '2023-07-02 18:00:00', '2024-02-02 18:00:00', '2023-09-05 22:56:26', '2023-09-07 04:35:05'),
(74, 'Bachelor of Science', 'Computer Science (ORE)', 'Computer science at the School of Electrical Engineering and Computer Science combines the study of computation and information processing fundamentals with their application. Computer scientists build fast, reliable, scalable and secure software systems to organize and analyze information. The honours curriculum comprises advanced topics in databases, artificial intelligence, computer graphics, security, distributed computing and algorithm design, culminating in an honours project.\r\n\r\nThis program teaches graduates how to use their creative and innovative talents to conceive, design and implement software systems. The University of Ottawa\'s degrees are very flexible and include options, minors and a major, which can be used to explore connections between computer science and many other fields of study.', 1, 3, 4, '$13,213.00 CAD / Year', '3 year bachelor\'s degree', 'Grade 12 / High School, Minimum GPA 95.0%, IELTS 6.5', '$55,606.00 CAD / Year', '$256.00 CAD', 'Sept 2024', 'https://admin.edumatric.com/uploads/coursedocument/B7nJ9XxmOgGJDrAe7U4CN7DJVZZgGb3VycZbWbIz.png', '2024-04-30 18:00:00', '2024-05-31 18:00:00', '2023-09-05 22:58:56', '2023-09-05 22:58:56'),
(75, 'MA in Economics', 'Master of Arts in Economics', 'A master\'s degree in economics from Central Michigan University is a stepping-stone to a the doctoral program of your choice. Lay the groundwork here for a career in business, academia or government.\r\nA master\'s in economics is a necessary step for many careers in the field. Whether you pursue doctoral work or a job after graduating, CMU will give you the quantitative and data analysis skills you\'ll need to thrive.\r\nAt CMU, you\'ll work closely with faculty as you learn to conduct independent research. That collaboration is the hallmark of CMU\'s graduate program in economics. Many students co-author papers with faculty, and publish in peer-reviewed journals. That provides invaluable experience developing research skills and navigating the publication process.\r\nCMU\'s economics program is very much international. About two-thirds of your colleagues will come from foreign countries. In the past, students have hailed from China, Romania, Ghana, India and elsewhere.\r\nWhile most students go on to pursue a Ph.D., you may choose to go into business. Many employers in the private, non-profit, and government sectors are eager to hire employees with the knowledge and leadership skills you\'ll have. You may also opt to pursue a graduate certificate in data mining, which extends your analytical skills with coursework in statistics, actuarial and data sciences; computer science; and geography and environmental studies.\r\nAccelerated Master option is available for this course', 2, 2, 26, '$22000 per Year', '2 Years', '4 years Bachelor\'s Degree with CGPA 2.7 and IELTS 6.5', '28,710 per course', '$60', '2024-01-08, 2024-08-26,2025-01-13', 'https://admin.edumatric.com/uploads/coursedocument/VqC3onH4wL2jDjneQs6kh0GAF2krWJLFwxwD3TY5.png', '2023-01-06 18:00:00', '2024-10-01 18:00:00', '2023-09-05 23:00:38', '2023-09-07 02:57:10'),
(76, 'Master of Business Administration', 'Sport and Recreation Management', 'Interested applicants can turn their passion for sports and recreation into a fulfilling career with Canada\'s only MBA in Sports and Recreation Management at the University of New Brunswick.\r\n\r\nIn this program students will combine courses from the Faculty of Management’s MBA program and from the Faculty of Kinesiology, giving them a unique education that fills an important gap in the sports and recreation industry.\r\n\r\nIn year one of the program, students will develop a “business tool kit” by taking business courses in\r\n\r\nAccounting\r\nBusiness Law\r\nFinance\r\nMarketing\r\nManagement of Information Systems\r\nOperations Management\r\nStatistics\r\nThis tool kit builds leadership skills students can use in any industry, but in year two of the program, students will learn how to use them in the sports and recreation industry by taking kinesiology courses in\r\n\r\nFoundations of Sport and Recreation\r\nTrends and Issues in Sport and Recreation\r\nSport Marketing\r\nCareers and People Management in Sport and Recreation\r\nIn their final semester, students can network with professionals and gain real-world industry experience through an internship. UNB students have interned with such organizations as\r\n\r\nAtlantic Rugby Canada\r\nCanadian Football League\r\nCanadian Paralympic Committee\r\nCanadian Sport Centre\r\nCity of Fredericton Sport Tourism\r\nCommonwealth Games Canada\r\nGrootbos Foundation, South Africa\r\nLancaster Inferno, USA\r\nOrr Hockey Group\r\nOttawa Senators\r\nParticipACTION\r\nRight to Play\r\nTrojan One (T1) Sport Marketing\r\nGraduates with an MBA in Sports and Recreation Management are qualified for positions in management, accounting, marketing, advertising, public relations and sales operations.\r\n\r\nEmployers looking for this unique set of skills include a variety of profit and not-for-profit organizations including sports teams, professional athletes, sports associations, sports and tourism organization, arenas, auditoriums, stadiums, colleges and universities, health clubs and sports facilities.\r\n\r\nSome positions for which this degree will prepare students include\r\n\r\nAthletics director\r\nEvent organizer\r\nEvent marketing director\r\nMarketing director for sports teams\r\nParks and recreation director\r\nSports and wellness director\r\nSports marketing and research\r\nSports agent\r\nSports finance/marketing/advertising executive\r\nSports facilities manager\r\nSports fundraising manager\r\nSports fundraising director\r\nSports franchise director\r\n*The Faculty of Management at the University of New Brunswick Fredericton is AACSB Accredited. AACSB accreditation is known worldwide as the longest-standing, most recognized form of specialized accreditation that an institution and its business programs can earn.', 1, 2, 25, '$10,000.00 CAD / Year', NULL, '4-Year Bachelor\'s Degree, Minimum GPA 73.0%,IELTS 7', '$18,610.00 CAD / Year', '$125.00 CAD', 'Sep 2024', 'https://admin.edumatric.com/uploads/coursedocument/jWpsHQuQGZWKQCL09s0DuBOrxyzgjfqgspBkbqvM.png', '2023-07-03 18:00:00', '2024-01-31 18:00:00', '2023-09-05 23:03:42', '2023-09-05 23:03:42'),
(77, 'Bachelor of Science (Honours) - Computer Science (ORC) (Optional Co-op)', 'Computer Science (ORC) (Optional Co-op)', 'Computer science at the School of Electrical Engineering and Computer Science combines the study of computation and information processing fundamentals with their application in the world around. Computer scientists build fast, reliable, scalable and secure software systems to organize and analyze information. The honours curriculum comprises advanced topics in databases, artificial intelligence, computer graphics, security, distributed computing and algorithm design, culminating in an honours project. \r\n\r\nThis program teaches graduates how to use their creative and innovative talents to conceive, design and implement software systems. The French Immersion Stream is now available to all students in the Computer Science program. University of Ottawa’s degrees are very flexible and include options, minors and a major, which can be used to explore connections between computer science and many other fields of study.', 1, 1, 4, '$13,213.00 CAD / Year', '4  year bachelor\'s degree', 'Grade 12 / High School, Minimum GPA 95.0%, IELTS 6.5', '$40,339.00 CAD / Year', '$256.00 CAD', 'Sept 2024', 'https://admin.edumatric.com/uploads/coursedocument/BdTO39r88EF27mwHvSECc23TgqWqKLKYj0EFEeGF.png', '2023-09-05 18:00:00', '2023-09-05 18:00:00', '2023-09-05 23:04:15', '2023-09-05 23:04:15');
