(423, 'International Year One + Bachelor of Arts - Global Tourism Management', 'Global Tourism Management', 'Students can gain the English language, study skills and academic knowledge needed to enter into an undergraduate degree at Royal Roads University. As part of this three semester program they will study a range of academic subjects that will develop their English language, quantitative, analytical and interpersonal skills. These skills will provide students with the base for successfully completing an undergraduate degree.\r\nInternational year one is a pathway program for international those who want to study an undergraduate degree at Royal Roads University, but do not have a diploma required for direct entry. \r\n\r\nThe Bachelor of Arts in Global Tourism Management (BAGTM) program ­focuses on global tourism opportunities, trends and issues that will ensure students will have the tools and knowledge to advance their career in tourism and hospitality anywhere in the world. They will not only learn to use entrepreneurship, leadership, and management skills to contribute to community and business development.\r\n\r\nExperiential learning is an important component of this program; graduates will be taken out of the classroom and exposed to actual tourism operations and situations through a 1-week field trip course. Here they will explore some of the best that Vancouver Island has to offer, including the beaches of Tofino and slopes of Mount Washington. Graduates will meet tourism entrepreneurs and professionals to better understand the issues and realities faced by the tourism industry. They will learn the practical aspects of travel management and tour operations while travelling to different destinations on Vancouver Island.\r\n\r\nAs a BAGTM student, graduates will have the opportunity to benefit from a perspective-shifting experience by studying a semester abroad at any of our partner universities in Korea, India, Austria, Germany, Chile, or Vietnam. This program component will provide them with customizable study option to expand their international experience and cultural relevancy.', 1, 1, 70, '$12,960.00 CAD / Year', '4 year bachelor\'s degree including internships', 'Grade 12 / High School, Minimum GPA  73.0%, IELTS 6.5', '$224,450.00 CAD / Year', '$131.39 CAD', 'SEPT 2024', 'https://admin.edumatric.com/uploads/coursedocument/w4wxzCFvGYRQ7UTsXrqEq0dja69PXms379V3XO31.png', '2023-09-09 18:00:00', '2023-09-09 18:00:00', '2023-09-09 23:16:08', '2023-09-09 23:16:08'),
(424, 'Master of Business Analytics', 'Master of Business Analytics (Extension)', 'The Master of Business Analytics (Extension) is a unique transdisciplinary program of study in business analytics. With subjects drawn from UTS Business School, the Faculty of Engineering and Information Technology and the TD School, students are provided with a course structure which fits their background and experience, as well as flexible specialisations to meet new needs and career interests. The course is delivered in blended mode, combining contemporary online and face-to-face learning experiences in UTS\'s leading-edge facilities.\r\n\r\nThe course is suitable for students from both business and IT backgrounds who seek to upskill and develop the skills required to meet the growth in emerging careers in business analytics.\r\n\r\nCourse Duration: 2 years full time or 4 years part time.', 3, 2, 60, '$1500+ (AUD)', '2 Years', '4 years Bachelor\'s Degree & IELTS: 6.5 overall with a writing score of 6.0', '$91,584 per course (AUD)', '$50 AUD', '2024-02-19', 'https://admin.edumatric.com/uploads/coursedocument/aIfouiBK1BLdWkZ9x833MdYi4r37CZkPufDfFz8g.png', '2023-02-19 18:00:00', '2023-11-29 18:00:00', '2023-09-09 23:26:09', '2023-09-09 23:35:40'),
(425, 'MA in Property Development and Investment', 'Master of Property Development and Investment', 'This course is designed for both property and real estate investment practitioners, and graduates in related fields who wish to extend their qualifications and expertise in property development and investment. Graduates have a commitment to professionalism in the property and real estate investment sectors. This course is for property and investment professionals who want to upgrade their qualifications or expertise or for those who wish to enter the property and real estate investment industries. In the first year students develop an understanding of how to balance private and public interests in urban development, how to evaluate real estate assets, and how to assess development feasibility.\r\nCourse Duration: 2 years full time or 4 years part time.', 3, 2, 60, '$1500+ (AUD)', '2 Years', '4 years Bachelor\'s Degree & IELTS: 6.5 overall with a writing score of 6.0', '$76,608 per course (AUD)', '$50 AUD', '2024-02-19, 2024-08-05', 'https://admin.edumatric.com/uploads/coursedocument/GRMMzSOHjwuBEMTBq3PKOPActJdxMk1NIsQFlWia.png', '2023-02-19 18:00:00', '2024-04-29 18:00:00', '2023-09-09 23:30:08', '2023-09-09 23:35:08'),
(426, 'Bachelor of Commerce', 'Bachelor of Commerce', 'The Bachelor of Commerce (BCom) will provide students with a broad foundation knowledge of contemporary business and its practices. Based in Vancouver, Canada, this ACBSP-accredited degree prepares students for a successful career in business or management, where they will contribute constructively to a global economy. University Canada West\'s BCom program has also received the NCMA designation from CIM | Chartered Managers Canada.\r\n\r\nStudents currently enrolled in the BCom program are entitled to a free Associate Membership with the association, giving University Canada West students the chance to belong to Canada’s chartered management and leadership association while earning their degree.\r\n\r\nAssociate Members can participate in all the networking and professional development opportunities the association offers, helping them get ready for their new career after they graduate.\r\n\r\nGraduates of the BCom program will:\r\n\r\nhave a comprehensive understanding of contemporary business practices across all areas of business management.\r\nknow how to conduct business in a multicultural environment, spanning international borders and working cross-culturally.\r\nhave the ability to use interdisciplinary approaches to solve problems and create new business opportunities.\r\nbe able to use critical thinking to analyze and interpret information to make informed decisions.', 1, 1, 9, '$13,213.00 CAD / Year', '4 year bachelor\'s degree including an optional practicum', 'Grade 12 / High School, Minimum GPA  60.0%, IELTS 6.5', '$20,180.00 CAD / Year', '$0.00 CAD', 'JAN 2024, APR 2024, JULY 2024', 'https://admin.edumatric.com/uploads/coursedocument/jWgf2S5MY5nLHxN4uK7J3QobGy8bMoCo90i0PKSp.png', '2023-09-09 18:00:00', '2023-09-09 18:00:00', '2023-09-09 23:34:33', '2023-09-09 23:34:33'),
(427, 'Bachelor of Arts - Business Communication', 'Business Communication', 'The Bachelor of Arts in Business Communication (BA) is an interdisciplinary program that will develop students\' knowledge of media, cultural studies and business alongside theoretical and practical skills. The communication methods learnt and media training students get throughout this course are relevant to careers in professional writing, journalism, public relations, communications, and advertising.\r\n\r\nGraduates of the BA program will be able to:\r\n\r\nLearn to evaluate and integrate all types of business communication.\r\nDemonstrate research techniques and methodologies.\r\nCreate ethically and legally sound content for a variety of markets.\r\nIntegrate media and content to communicate persuasively to specific audiences.\r\nApply communication methods to business problems and contexts.', 1, 1, 9, '$13,213.00 CAD / Year', '4 year bachelor\'s degree including an optional internship', 'Grade 12 / High School, Minimum GPA  60.0%, IELTS 6.5', '$20,180.00 CAD / Year', '$0.00 CAD', 'JAN 2024, APR 2024, JULY 2024, SEPT 2024', 'https://admin.edumatric.com/uploads/coursedocument/l8HszZpqSclAlTtmVKsZNgKw0qlvViZ2Bc0GaaYL.png', '2023-09-09 18:00:00', '2023-09-09 18:00:00', '2023-09-09 23:37:31', '2023-09-09 23:37:31'),
(428, 'Bachelor of Science (Honours) - Computer Science (G400)', 'Computer Science', 'Computer science is a dynamic discipline with a diverse range of applications and career paths. This program explores the theory and practice of innovative and experimental computer science, allowing students to develop well-rounded professional and technical skills.\r\n\r\nThis Computer Science program is accredited by the British Computing Society (BCS), and provides students with the knowledge and skills required to become a computing professional. Students will learn to work effectively in a professional software and systems development environment. Delivering a broad yet rigorous grounding in computer science, this program uses both theoretical and practical learning approaches. Students will gain cutting-edge knowledge and skills through state-of-the-art equipment and expert teaching offered at the School of Computing and Communications.\r\n\r\nIn the first year, students will receive a comprehensive understanding of the fundamental principles of the discipline, combined with their modern day application. Throughout their study, students will gain skills and experience from a range of modules, including Software Development, Information Systems, and Digital Systems. Taking a practical approach to education, students are encouraged to build and analyse systems and software, as well as work with end user feedback to refine and adapt solutions.\r\n\r\nAfter gaining an overview of the subject in the first year, students will be motivated by topics that become progressively deeper and more specialised as their skills develop throughout second and third year. In addition to progressing their foundational understanding, programming, and software design skills, students will explore social, ethical and professional issues related to the discipline and will complete a group project. This will prepare students for and give them experience of computing in the real-world.\r\n\r\nThe final year will also give students the opportunity to explore a range of well-constructed and enriching optional modules, as well as undertaking an individual project. On this project, students will work closely with one of Lancaster University\'s academics, allowing students to use and further develop the skills acquired throughout their degree.', 1, 3, 72, '£12,180.00 GBP / Year', '3 year bachelor\'s degree including an optional work experience', 'Grade 12 / High School, Minimum GPA  75.0%, IELTS 6', '£26,550.00 GBP / Year', '£0.00 GBP', 'OCT 2024', 'https://admin.edumatric.com/uploads/coursedocument/LVars3Y8aNDNaDxNFrzXgKdDl1vYvzqOu3N7UtAJ.png', '2023-09-09 18:00:00', '2023-09-09 18:00:00', '2023-09-09 23:50:10', '2023-09-09 23:50:10'),
(429, 'Bachelor of Business Administration (BBA)', 'BBA', 'Business plays a major role in the structure and functioning of contemporary society. Rapid changes in technology, resource allocation, structural shifts in the economy, changes in consumer preferences, global competition, and shifts in the employment market all necessitate a better understanding of the role and nature of business in today’s society.\r\n\r\nThe BBA provides a well-rounded business education with a focus on global business operations, emerging markets, and technology-enabled organizations. Students develop an in-depth understanding of one of the business majors and learn a broad range of managerial capabilities, problem solving and communication skills. Electives allow flexibility, adaptability and creativity and prepare graduates for diverse careers in global management, administration, and entrepreneurship, as well as a range of postgraduate opportunities.\r\n\r\nVIU’s Bachelor of Business Administration (BBA) allows electives to improve students’ understanding of the intellectual and applied linkages between Social Sciences, Humanities and Business. Students will develop an appreciation and understanding of how to achieve organizational objectives in an often diverse and turbulent external environment. Lectures are augmented by seminars, research projects and computer simulations. Students are encouraged to take electives from the Social Sciences and Humanities.\r\n\r\nThe Bachelor of Business Administration program offers the following Majors:\r\nAccounting\r\nEconomics\r\nFinancial Services\r\nHuman Resource Management\r\nInternational Business\r\nManagement\r\nMarketing\r\nPlease  note: The Business Administration program offers an exit point after Year 2. Students can graduate at the end of Year 2 with a Business Administration Diploma or go on to complete the additional two years to graduate with the Bachelor of Business Administration (BBA) degree', 1, 1, 73, '$12,669.00 CAD / Year', '4 year bachelor\'s degree including an optional internship  Program', 'Grade 12 / High School, Minimum GPA  50.0%, IELTS 6.5', '$21,741.00 CAD / Year', '$150.00 CAD', 'JAN 2024, SEPT 2024', 'https://admin.edumatric.com/uploads/coursedocument/449LEBFwlA0ZnbKNL4pSL4i63D6fSeO0SXsfBsIe.png', '2023-09-09 18:00:00', '2023-09-09 18:00:00', '2023-09-10 00:29:30', '2023-09-10 00:29:30'),
(430, 'Bachelor of Science - Computer Science (Optional Co-op)', 'Computer Science', 'Computing Science is a rapidly-growing field, generating a great number of employment opportunities. Government agencies are predicting shortages of qualified computing people that will number in the tens of thousands in Canada alone. The Bachelor of Science, Major in Computing Science, is designed to meet the training and educational requirements outlined by CIPS (Canadian Information Processing Society), ACM (Association for Computing Machinery), and IEEE (Institute of Electrical and Electronics Engineers). These requirements reflect the needs of the computing industry, both nationally and internationally.\r\n\r\nThe program is composed of courses drawn from the systems, theoretical and business application domains. It is designed to train students in applied computing and educate them in the social, ethical and legal implications of computing.', 1, 1, 73, '$12,669.00 CAD / Year', '4 year bachelor\'s degree', 'Grade 12 / High School, Minimum GPA  50.0%, IELTS 6.5', '$21,741.00 CAD / Year', '$150.00 CAD', 'SEPT 2024', 'https://admin.edumatric.com/uploads/coursedocument/OAHprO2oDr1AfU2ze0Rw15GOxzeCa44LBPXSiW86.png', '2023-09-09 18:00:00', '2023-09-09 18:00:00', '2023-09-10 00:31:05', '2023-09-10 00:31:05'),
(431, 'Bachelor of Science - Geoscience', 'Geoscience', 'The BSc Major in Geoscience is a 4 year program that will provide students with a broad foundation in the geosciences, drawing upon the expertise and experience of the instructors within the Earth Science and Geography departments at VIU. The program will provide students with an understanding of core geoscience concepts such as the scientific method, Earth systems, the age of Earth, water cycling on Earth, evolution of life on Earth, natural resources and energy, natural disasters and human impacts on Earth environments. The program will give students the opportunity to apply their knowledge with hands-on activities both in the lab and in the field, and will direct students towards independent research and enquiry. Student will be expected to achieve a high-quality of written and communication skills during their geoscience studies. One of the main themes of the BSc Major is \"Environmental Geoscience\", as this reflects the expertise of the Earth Science and Geography departments, VIU\'s location on the west coast of British Columbia, and a demand for this expertise in the job market.', 1, 1, 73, '$12,669.00 CAD / Year', '4 year bachelor\'s degree', 'Grade 12 / High School, Minimum GPA  50.0%, IELTS 6.5', '$19,227.00 CAD / Year', '$150.00 CAD', 'SEPT 2024', 'https://admin.edumatric.com/uploads/coursedocument/PbZd1oVlzdhb1W1QyNXkOi1oNpxT0bMty00Hiq6c.png', '2023-09-09 18:00:00', '2023-09-09 18:00:00', '2023-09-10 00:33:22', '2023-09-10 00:33:22'),
(432, 'Bachelor of Business Administration', 'BBA', 'Yukon\'s Business programs are grounded in the rich history of the Yukon and guided by the spirit of reconciliation. They offer on-the-land learning, capstone-style courses and classwork that will prepare students to lead diverse organizations and build prosperous communities.\r\n\r\nYukon College’s Bachelor of Business Administration (BBA) aims to create business leaders that will increase prosperity where they live and work. Many northern rural and remote areas of Canada and the world are well positioned to expand, develop and provide rich and rewarding places to live and work. This degree is created for those interested in making a difference in these places. Students will be exposed to values, knowledge and skills that prepare them to work well and collaboratively within the business and governance context of the north. \r\n\r\nThis BBA is distinctive in that it has been created from a de-colonial perspective. The curriculum is rooted in the context of a unique identity and circumstances that are common to much of the world.  The identity is closely tied to the land and wilderness, and to First Nations’ traditions and cultures. However, many of the circumstances that define many is not unique to Yukon; low population densities, vast distances and remoteness, higher costs, and operating environments that often require people to work independently while fulfilling broad roles are common beyond urban center\'s. \r\n\r\nThe programs balance the academic rigor necessary for baccalaureate-level training while fostering communal growth through experiential learning and creating a supportive learning community. Graduates leave Yukon College prepared to create and sustain prosperity in places they call home.', 1, 1, 74, '$12,960.00 CAD / Year', '4 year bachelor\'s degree', 'Grade 12 / High School, Minimum GPA  50.0%, IELTS 6.5', '$12,000.00 CAD / Year', '$100.00 CAD', 'SEPT 2024', 'https://admin.edumatric.com/uploads/coursedocument/RML3fa9Ngmmy8kHqkbKy7wU6gMDAWtvQVc86onXt.png', '2023-09-09 18:00:00', '2023-09-09 18:00:00', '2023-09-10 00:41:17', '2023-09-10 00:41:17'),
(433, 'Bachelor of Commerce (Honours) - International Management and Technology (3 years)', 'International Management and Technology', 'International Business University\'s Bachelor of Commerce (Honours) in International Management and Technology degree responds to the needs of Canadian and international employers for graduates who combine business knowledge, soft skills and technical skills and who are able to transition seamlessly into the workplace\r\n\r\nEquipped with business knowledge together with the most relevant technologies, students will develop the knowledge, skills, attitudes and behaviours that employers are looking for today. Graduates will be able to apply both their knowledge and interpersonal skills in integrated projects alongside a capstone course incorporated into the curriculum.\r\n\r\nIBU\'s BComm programs have been accredited by National Committee for Management Association (NCMA) in Canada. Students graduating from these programs will meet the academic requirements equivalent to the Chartered Management Program (CMP) framework. The CMP can lead to the Certified in Management (C.I.M.®) and Chartered Manager (C.Mgr.®) professional designations.\r\n\r\nFor May 2023 and September 2023 Intakes:\r\n\r\nEight Semester Tuition Schedule (with $9,000 bursary)\r\n\r\nSemester 1	$6,625.00\r\nSemester 5	$7,800.00\r\nSemester 2     $6,625.00\r\nSemester 6	$7,800.00\r\nSemester 3     $7,775.00\r\nSemester 7	$7,800.00\r\nSemester 4	$7,775.00\r\nSemester 8 	$7,800.00\r\nTotal Tuition: $60,000.00\r\n\r\n\r\nStudents wishing to enter International Business University whose IELTS score falls below 6.0 may enter International Business University under the following conditions:\r\n\r\n1. Students whose IELTS score (or equivalent) is 4.5 or higher but lower than 5.5 will have to successfully complete ESL Pathway program with their pathway partner, ILSC Education Group.\r\n\r\nStudents entering International Business University whose IELTS score (or equivalent) is 5.5 or higher but lower than 6.0 will enroll in International Business University\'s regular academic program and will enroll in an English for Academic Purposes course in Term 1.\r\n\r\nAll students will have access to on-going language training and support during their studies at International Business University.\r\n\r\nThe ESL Pathway Program is being offered at the ILSC Education Group.\r\n\r\n2. Students wishing to enter International Business University who do not have Grade 12 Math may enter International Business University under the following conditions:\r\n\r\nStudents who have not completed High School Math (Grade 12) will be enrolled in International Business University\'s regular academic program and will enroll in a Math for Business course in Term 1.\r\n\r\nStudents will have an opportunity to undertake a Math Challenge Exam during their Orientation Week for the waiver of the course.', 1, 3, 75, '$13,318.00 CAD / Year', '32 month bachelor\'s degree', 'Grade 12 / High School, Minimum GPA  55.0%, IELTS 6.5', '$13,250.00 CAD / Year', '$0.00 CAD', 'JAN 2024, MAY 2024', 'https://admin.edumatric.com/uploads/coursedocument/MTuJyryk02tOMVShVEHjQsbwqOV3NHorz2me7o8W.png', '2023-09-09 18:00:00', '2023-09-09 18:00:00', '2023-09-10 00:48:17', '2023-09-10 00:48:17'),
(434, 'Master\'s in  Event Management (Extension)', 'Master of Event Management (Extension)', 'The Master of Event Management (Extension) provides a substantial overview of the events industry and is designed to develop advanced professional skills and knowledge to sufficiently equip students for management positions in the broad and multifaceted events industry. With this in mind, the program includes subjects that seek to develop an understanding of event creation, planning, delivery, marketing and evaluation processes and practices of various forms of events in both Australian and international contexts. The course is designed to expose students to best practice, current issues, and emerging trends in event management. Industry experts are engaged throughout course and assessment design, as well as in subject delivery, to ensure the integration of real-world practice against cutting edge theory. Research-inspired course content is delivered by world-leading academics and industry partners. The course has a strong focus on professional practice, including two innovative capstone subjects – Industry Research Project or Internship Experience – which allow students to work either on or with contemporary industry issues and opportunities.\r\nCourse Duration: 2 years full time or 4 years part time.', 3, 2, 60, '$1500+ (AUD)', NULL, NULL, '$73,728 per course (AUD)', '$50 AUD', '2024-02-19', 'https://admin.edumatric.com/uploads/coursedocument/JrtWYn06MFEYuQFCcXNQcZ52X9vZz3lQndhSX651.jpg', '2023-02-19 18:00:00', '2023-11-29 18:00:00', '2023-09-10 01:05:39', '2023-09-10 01:05:39'),
(435, 'Bachelor of Business Administration (Optional Co-op)', 'BBA', 'The Faculty of Business is committed to providing students with a high quality, integrated business education in a personalized learning environment. UPEI\'s Bachelor of Business Administration (BBA) degree program is structured to provide the broad-based, cross-functional business education required for leaders of business, government, and not-for-profit organizations. The Faculty\'s personalized learning environment provides opportunities for extensive interaction between students, faculty and practitioners.\r\n\r\nThe Faculty of Business holds a unique position within the province’s education system. As the only university school of business, it is committed to intellectual leadership, and to excellence in developing new knowledge and conveying that knowledge to its students and to the public. In order to attract, develop and retain students, faculty and staff, the Faculty recognizes that it must sustain an intellectually stimulating environment.\r\n\r\nThe Faculty views its students not as customers, but rather as partners in the development of a high quality business education. Graduates are expected to have developed competency in integrating the core functional business disciplines; ethical, social, historical and global awareness; critical thinking and problem solving; quantitative analysis; communication skills and leadership; team work as well as personal initiative; technological application in business; and using business research to support evidence-informed practice.\r\n\r\nThe degree program in the Faculty of Business is designed to fulfill this mission and to provide the educational breadth and depth needed by business leaders.', 1, 1, 76, '$12,960.00 CAD / Year', '4 year bachelor\'s degree', 'Grade 12 / High School, Minimum GPA  70.0%, IELTS 6.5', '$14,838.00 CAD / Year', '$50.00 CAD', 'JAN 2024, SEPT 2024', 'https://admin.edumatric.com/uploads/coursedocument/KLeI4z3bGMuFxLo39qveUBSoGOgFfDUXdg9ZPkxc.png', '2023-09-09 18:00:00', '2023-09-09 18:00:00', '2023-09-10 02:31:37', '2023-09-10 02:31:37'),
(436, 'Bachelor of Business Administration - International Business (Optional Co-op)', 'BBA', 'The Faculty of Business is committed to providing students with a high quality, integrated business education in a personalized learning environment. Our Bachelor of Business Administration (BBA) degree program is structured to provide the broad-based, cross-functional business education required for leaders of business, government, and not-for-profit organizations. The Faculty\'s personalized learning environment provides opportunities for extensive interaction between students, faculty and practitioners.\r\n\r\nThe Faculty of Business holds a unique position within the province’s education system. As the only university school of business, it is committed to intellectual leadership, and to excellence in developing new knowledge and conveying that knowledge to its students and to the public. In order to attract, develop and retain students, faculty and staff, the Faculty recognizes that it must sustain an intellectually stimulating environment.\r\n\r\nThe Faculty views its students not as customers, but rather as partners in the development of a high quality business education. Graduates are expected to have developed competency in integrating the core functional business disciplines; ethical, social, historical and global awareness; critical thinking and problem solving; quantitative analysis; communication skills and leadership; team work as well as personal initiative; technological application in business; and using business research to support evidence-informed practice.\r\n\r\nThe degree program in the Faculty of Business is designed to fulfill this mission and to provide the educational breadth and depth needed by business leaders.', 1, 1, 76, '$12,960.00 CAD / Year  Cost of Living Gross Tuition', '4 year bachelor\'s degree', 'Grade 12 / High School, Minimum GPA  70.0%, IELTS 6.5', '$14,838.00 CAD / Year', '$50.00 CAD', 'JAN 2024, SEPT 2024', 'https://admin.edumatric.com/uploads/coursedocument/wqM3MpeHnYFSv5sEcQsEJPCxpBnQL9crZVxV0yYf.png', '2023-09-09 18:00:00', '2023-09-09 18:00:00', '2023-09-10 02:33:31', '2023-09-10 02:33:31'),
(437, 'Bachelor of Science - Computer Science (Optional Co-op)', 'Computer Science', 'Computer Science programs enable innovation and discovery in most fields. Computer science encompasses both theory and practice; theoretical ideas about how information is represented and processed, and practical techniques for creating new software. UPEI offers computer science degree options including honours, major, minor, specialization in video game programming, and co-operative education.\r\n\r\nMathematical and computational sciences are experiencing a “boom”. Everyone is collecting data, and they need people with the skills to manage, analyze, and extract useful information from the data. This is what mathematicians, statisticians, and computer scientists are trained to do.\r\n\r\nEmployment prospects are among the highest of any field, and Honours graduates are well positioned to pursue graduate studies.', 1, 1, 76, '$12,960.00 CAD / Year  Cost of Living  Gross Tuition', '4 year bachelor\'s degree', 'Grade 12 / High School, Minimum GPA  70.0%, IELTS 6.5', '$14,838.00 CAD / Year', '$50.00 CAD', 'JAN 2024, SEPT 2024', 'https://admin.edumatric.com/uploads/coursedocument/c45ai04valmPHGzkLZ55vs4t7RmnhkMjnjq5BKjN.png', '2023-09-09 18:00:00', '2023-09-09 18:00:00', '2023-09-10 02:37:35', '2023-09-10 02:37:35'),
(438, 'Bachelor of Business Administration - Accounting (Optional Co-op)', 'Accounting', 'The Faculty of Business is committed to providing students with a high quality, integrated business education in a personalized learning environment. UPEI\'s Bachelor of Business Administration (BBA) degree program is structured to provide the broad-based, cross-functional business education required for leaders of business, government, and not-for-profit organizations. The Faculty\'s personalized learning environment provides opportunities for extensive interaction between students, faculty and practitioners.\r\n\r\nThe Faculty of Business holds a unique position within the province’s education system. As the only university school of business, it is committed to intellectual leadership, and to excellence in developing new knowledge and conveying that knowledge to its students and to the public. In order to attract, develop and retain students, faculty and staff, the Faculty recognizes that it must sustain an intellectually stimulating environment.\r\n\r\nThe Faculty views its students not as customers, but rather as partners in the development of a high quality business education. Graduates are expected to have developed competency in integrating the core functional business disciplines; ethical, social, historical and global awareness; critical thinking and problem solving; quantitative analysis; communication skills and leadership; team work as well as personal initiative; technological application in business; and using business research to support evidence-informed practice.\r\n\r\nThe degree program in the Faculty of Business is designed to fulfill this mission and to provide the educational breadth and depth needed by business leaders.', 1, 1, 76, '$12,960.00 CAD / Year', '4 year bachelor\'s degree', 'Grade 12 / High School, Minimum GPA  70.0%, IELTS 6.5', '$14,274.00 CAD / Year', '$50.00 CAD', 'JAN 2024, SEPT 2024', 'https://admin.edumatric.com/uploads/coursedocument/GqJxGMsrRTg6JGoutwuSeRFnFf5NW3x24J1OefEE.png', '2023-09-09 18:00:00', '2023-09-09 18:00:00', '2023-09-10 02:38:58', '2023-09-10 02:38:58'),
(439, 'Bachelor of Business Administration (BBA) (Honours)', 'BBA', 'Tyndale University’s Bachelor of Business Administration (BBA) degree opens multiple career options in the public, private and nonprofit sectors. Students can expect to gain valuable leadership and management skills along with an in-depth understanding of business principles and practices. Faculty will help students solidify and meet their goals, and business professionals will provide networking opportunities and guidance along the way. Discover how to combine Christian ethics with business acumen to make positive economic, social, spiritual and environmental impacts on the world.', 1, 1, 77, '$13,318.00 CAD / Year', '4 year bachelor\'s degree', 'Grade 12 / High School, Minimum GPA  65.0%, IELTS 6.5', '$17,430.00 CAD / Year', '$150.00 CAD', 'Jan 2024 , Aug 2024, Sep 2024', 'https://admin.edumatric.com/uploads/coursedocument/0xFG3vhtZzITq7pwd5AFPpzV99ByiEOskzzCoOpf.png', '2023-09-09 18:00:00', '2023-09-09 18:00:00', '2023-09-10 02:47:08', '2023-09-10 02:47:08'),
(440, 'Bachelor of Business Administration (Optional Co-op)', 'BBA', 'Studying Business Administration prepares students for a wealth of career options. At Crandall’s Business School, business students have an opportunity to concentrate their business studies in Accounting, Economics & Finance, Marketing, or Management. Through the program students will learn to communicate clearly, analyze organizational issues, resolve business challenges and identify best business practices.\r\n\r\nThe tools and skills students gain at Crandall University’s Business School will equip them to succeed in a demanding career or to pursue Graduate Studies.\r\n\r\nProgram highlights:\r\nCrandall University’s Business School also offers the BBA Cooperative Education degree that, through on-the-job experience, provides students with the opportunity to put learning into practice while developing important career-building network connections Co-op students alternate study semesters with three work-terms during which they earn money. At the Business School, students regularly compete in case competitions. Recently, Crandall University students placed in the top three in the regional Entrepreneur Contest and went on to the national competition.\r\nComplete a business internship for credit, students who wish. Past internships have included such activities as completing an organizational design and implementation, and working in an HR department’s policy area.\r\nJoin the Business Society, an active campus organization that includes both social activities and support for the group’s charitable projects.', 1, 1, 78, '$13,310.00 CAD / Year  Cost of Living  Gross Tuition', '4 year bachelor\'s degree', 'Grade 12 / High School, Minimum GPA  70.0%, IELTS 6.5', '$17,900.00 CAD / Year', '$100.00 CAD', 'SEPT 2024', 'https://admin.edumatric.com/uploads/coursedocument/jpFfMf4rQnOKViihHUUbtRtPl0P3I99tafT2YTiK.png', '2023-09-09 18:00:00', '2023-09-09 18:00:00', '2023-09-10 02:51:39', '2023-09-10 02:51:39'),
(441, 'Bachelor of Arts - Environment and Society', 'Environment and Society', 'The Environment and Society Program is an interdisciplinary program with courses from several departments which explore the root causes of environmental degradation and how society can address them.\r\n\r\nCourses in Environment and Society at STU are designed around four pillars:\r\nProblems\r\nPerspectives\r\nPolitics\r\nPraxis—reflection and action for social change\r\nThe course focus on tracing the root causes of an issue and using knowledge to create social change is what sets our Environment and Society program apart.\r\n\r\nStudying Environment and Society will give students the ability to look at issues critically to understand causes and discover realistic solutions. They will develop advanced skills in research, as well as written and verbal communication, problem solving, and advocacy. Environment and Society graduates are able to connect their in-class learning to the real world and become effective ecological citizens.  \r\n\r\nThis prepares graduates for meaningful careers in fields like: \r\nGovernment\r\nBusiness\r\nNon-Governmental Organizations\r\nPublic Policy\r\nEnvironmental Law\r\nActivism\r\nEducation\r\nJournalism', 1, 1, 79, '$12,960.00 CAD / Year', '4 year bachelor\'s degree with an optional internship  Program', 'Grade 12 / High School, Minimum GPA  70.0%, IELTS 6.5', '$18,610.00 CAD / Year', '$0.00 CAD', 'JAN 2024, SEPT 2024', 'https://admin.edumatric.com/uploads/coursedocument/BDrN6O5eZY84hNTqeRaWJuyqpWlEyLPL1my6Aumy.png', '2023-09-09 18:00:00', '2023-09-09 18:00:00', '2023-09-10 02:56:33', '2023-09-10 02:56:33'),
(442, 'Bachelor of Science - Computer Science (Optional Co-op)', 'Computer Science', 'Computer technology is growing rapidly and affecting the lives of people in many different ways. The computer is a powerful tool for storing, retrieving, manipulating and presenting data. A special by-product of studying computer science is the learning and developing of an ability to solve the problems that are important in today’s changing world. In first year computer science, students will learn the Java programming language. The course is designed to challenge people who are fond of computers and mathematics, and possess the ability to think logically. Students with these interests or abilities will find computer science courses fascinating.', 1, 1, 80, '$13,213.00 CAD / Year', '4 year bachelor\'s degree', 'Grade 12 / High School, Minimum GPA  50.0%, IELTS 6.5', '$19,573.00 CAD / Year', '$140.00 CAD', 'SEPT 2024', 'https://admin.edumatric.com/uploads/coursedocument/LAGLt1SwZbo3E0UKz3OZkl2lC7XIHn8WMo2r170z.png', '2023-09-09 18:00:00', '2023-09-09 18:00:00', '2023-09-10 03:05:15', '2023-09-10 03:05:15'),
(443, 'Bachelor of Science - Environmental Science', 'Environmental Science', 'Environmental Science is the interdisciplinary study of the environment, its functioning and its relationship to human activities. It encompasses many of the traditional science disciplines, but uses these in the study of terrestrial, aquatic and atmospheric systems and their interactions. An Environmental Science graduate will have an in-depth knowledge of environmental systems but also of the breadth and context in which these systems operate. Students will develop the wide range of expertise necessary to address present and future environmental problems.\r\n\r\nBSES students must complete required courses in biology, chemistry, geology, geography, English, economics, and environmental ethics. In addition, they can select 18 credit hours of courses from one of the following areas of concentration: Biology, Chemistry, Geography, Applied Disaster and Emergency Studies, or Geology.', 1, 1, 80, '$13,213.00 CAD / Year', '4 year bachelor\'s degree', 'Grade 12 / High School, Minimum GPA  50.0%, IELTS 6.5', '$16,156.00 CAD / Year', '$140.00 CAD', 'SEPT 2024', 'https://admin.edumatric.com/uploads/coursedocument/CFm4QiIjju9qb0AjBKLRhc6B8sqJTCVwx9mkLtbO.png', '2023-09-09 18:00:00', '2023-09-09 18:00:00', '2023-09-10 03:06:53', '2023-09-10 03:06:53'),
(444, 'Bachelor of Science - Environmental Science', 'Environmental Science', 'Environmental Science is the interdisciplinary study of the environment, its functioning and its relationship to human activities. It encompasses many of the traditional science disciplines, but uses these in the study of terrestrial, aquatic and atmospheric systems and their interactions. An Environmental Science graduate will have an in-depth knowledge of environmental systems but also of the breadth and context in which these systems operate. Students will develop the wide range of expertise necessary to address present and future environmental problems.\r\n\r\nBSES students must complete required courses in biology, chemistry, geology, geography, English, economics, and environmental ethics. In addition, they can select 18 credit hours of courses from one of the following areas of concentration: Biology, Chemistry, Geography, Applied Disaster and Emergency Studies, or Geology.', 1, 1, 80, '$13,213.00 CAD / Year', '4 year bachelor\'s degree', 'Grade 12 / High School, Minimum GPA  50.0%, IELTS 6.5', '$16,156.00 CAD / Year', '$140.00 CAD', 'SEPT 2024', 'https://admin.edumatric.com/uploads/coursedocument/ZNCjtRYykZblUkLjts2XtjueJW7beiLoCFXuD4vx.png', '2023-09-09 18:00:00', '2023-09-09 18:00:00', '2023-09-10 03:06:54', '2023-09-10 03:06:54'),
(445, 'Bachelor of Business Administration', 'BBA', 'The aims of the programs offered are:\r\n\r\nTo prepare students for careers in Management, Entrepreneurship, or Accounting and for further study in Accounting, Management and other specialized disciplines within Business Administration.\r\nTo foster analytical, written, and oral skills essential for success in a rapidly changing economy and business world.\r\nTo provide students with a solid foundation in business and management and to foster awareness of the historical, economic, political, and philosophical context in which individuals, business, and societies function.\r\nThe Business Administration degrees are highly structured, as the capstone courses integrate concepts from all the functional areas of business. Students planning to major in Business Administration through any of the degree options must consult with the student advisor, or alternate, for the Business Administration Department for assistance in designing their programs, prior to registering for business courses. Care must be taken to ensure all required prerequisites are satisfied in order to complete the degree on schedule. Occasional variations in the program may be allowed with the permission of the Department and the Dean.', 1, 1, 80, '$13,213.00 CAD / Year', '4 year bachelor\'s degree', 'Grade 12 / High School, Minimum GPA  50.0%, IELTS 6.5', '$15,851.00 CAD / Year', '$140.00 CAD', 'SEPT 2024', 'https://admin.edumatric.com/uploads/coursedocument/5cRgtyahSti6uuUkHhEGteVFP27tf55JB2fC5D3d.png', '2023-09-09 18:00:00', '2023-09-09 18:00:00', '2023-09-10 03:08:59', '2023-09-10 03:08:59'),
(446, 'Bachelor of Tourism and Hospitality Management - General Studies (Co-op)', 'Tourism and Hospitality Management', 'Tourism is about more than hotels, restaurants and resorts. It\'s excursion and adventure tour companies, bed and breakfasts, experiences and memories that last a lifetime. Tourism is the world\'s largest service industry and careers in tourism and hospitality are available locally and around the world. In Nova Scotia, the tourism and hospitality industry is an exciting, vibrant and rapidly growing sector. Students in this program benefit from small class sizes and faculty who have a wide range of research interests and industry experience. \r\nAt the Mount, students will gain relevant work experience while they study through the co-operative education or practica programs. Growing industry network is an important part of being a Mount student, and the faculty and staff make every effort to ensure students have ample opportunities to connect with industry professionals at various points throughout the year.', 1, 1, 81, '$13,310.00 CAD / Year  Cost of Living   Gross Tuition', '4 year bachelor\'s degree including 12 month of co-op', 'Grade 12 / High School, Minimum GPA  70.0%, IELTS 6.5', '$17,855.00 CAD / Year', '$40.00 CAD', 'MAY 2024, SEP 2024', 'https://admin.edumatric.com/uploads/coursedocument/mgRKl3JhVc3J7oi6NUOqZbNyUPvUmAU7HDxx0gq8.png', '2023-09-09 18:00:00', '2023-09-09 18:00:00', '2023-09-10 03:21:28', '2023-09-10 03:21:28'),
(447, 'Bachelor of Business Administration - Management (Optional Co-Op)', 'Management', 'There are so many avenues open to students when they graduate with an education in Management from the Mount. Students could forge a career in human resource management, or compensation, or benefits administration. Or they could become an entrepreneur and run their own business. Or students could complete a professional management credential in areas such as the Institute of Canadian Bankers, the Insurance Institute of Canada, the Purchasing Management Association of Canada, and the Association of Administrative Assistants. At the Mount students can choose a major, a minor, or a concentration in management in the Bachelor of Business Administration degree.', 1, 1, 81, '$13,310.00 CAD / Year', '4 year bachelor\'s degree', 'Grade 12 / High School, Minimum GPA  70.0%, IELTS 6.5', '$17,855.00 CAD / Year', '$40.00 CAD', 'MAY 2024, SEP 2024', 'https://admin.edumatric.com/uploads/coursedocument/cZuEFl7Qf18EaxQXYgTpVJSgr6e428MWGnX1xQY2.png', '2023-09-09 18:00:00', '2023-09-09 18:00:00', '2023-09-10 03:24:23', '2023-09-10 03:24:23'),
(448, 'Bachelor of Business Administration - Accounting (Optional Co-Op)', 'Accounting', 'Accountants are responsible for the financial statements produced by businesses, government offices, and non-profit organizations. This is an exciting and growing industry with a clear career path to place students in a well paying, well respected, career.\r\n\r\nWith an accounting degree students can continue on to pursue a professional credential, such as a Chartered Accountant (CA), Certified Management Accountant (CMA), or a Certified General Accountant (CGA). It can also lead to becoming a Chief Financial Officer or even a CEO.', 1, 1, 81, '$13,310.00 CAD / Year', '4 year bachelor\'s degree', 'Grade 12 / High School, Minimum GPA  70.0%, IELTS 6.5', '$17,335.00 CAD / Year', '$40.00 CAD', 'MAY 2024, SEPT 2024', 'https://admin.edumatric.com/uploads/coursedocument/n1p3DUJeOq8ScFkdJUE0eWzZcr3L0sMhYfx9pR0F.png', '2023-09-09 18:00:00', '2023-09-09 18:00:00', '2023-09-10 03:26:53', '2023-09-10 03:26:53'),
(449, 'Bachelor of Business Administration - Human Resource Management (Optional Co-Op)', 'BBA', 'Students will learn how to determine an organization’s human resource needs and guide both employees and management through the internal and external demands of an ever-changing environment everyone must operate within with a major, concentration, or minor in Human Resource Management.\r\n\r\nThis specialty area of study provides relevant knowledge in the areas of human resource management strategy, recruitment, training and development, compensation management, labor relations, managing diversity, organizational topics, organizational behavior, values in a business society, international human resource development, and organizational change.', 1, 1, 81, '$13,310.00 CAD / Year', '4 year bachelor\'s degree', 'Grade 12 / High School, Minimum GPA  70.0%, IELTS 6.5', '$17,335.00 CAD / Yea', '$40.00 CAD', 'MAY 2024, SEPT 2024', 'https://admin.edumatric.com/uploads/coursedocument/c9M556Oj9a6T5O8TL4wJMe09vxEGBOLxFhShmwuS.png', '2023-09-09 18:00:00', '2023-09-09 18:00:00', '2023-09-10 03:29:21', '2023-09-10 03:29:21'),
(450, 'Master of Arts', 'Criminal Justice', 'This 30-credit program is designed especially for individuals looking to combine their academic and professional experience in the areas of criminal justice, social justice, or community justice in a way that suits their career plans. This program provides students with the knowledge and skills to develop evidence-based policies and practices for the purpose of contributing to the development of a more effective, efficient, and innovative criminal justice system. The program provides students with applied learning and the ability to further their educational and professional goals, and is an excellent opportunity for networking with other criminal justice professionals.\r\n\r\nThis program is ideal for students who wish to continue working full time while completing graduate studies. Students complete the program over 20 months and are required to attend courses three days a month (typically the first Thursday, Friday, and Saturday of each month). In the fifth and final semester, students write and present a major paper or thesis. It is normally expected that students will have completed a substantial amount of work on their major paper or thesis prior to starting their fifth semester. Students who do not complete their major paper or thesis in their final semester are required to extend their involvement in the program and be subject to continuance fees.', 1, 2, 82, '$12,960.00 CAD / Year', '20 month master\'s degree', '4-Year Bachelor\'s Degree, Minimum GPA 73.0%,IELTS 6.5', '$14,177.00 CAD / Year', '$250.00 CAD', 'Sep 2024', 'https://admin.edumatric.com/uploads/coursedocument/psCStO4ingwXzkkM7rppg666Z6EPQ6mhZ8giabLI.png', '2023-09-30 18:00:00', '2024-03-09 18:00:00', '2023-09-10 04:02:17', '2023-09-10 04:02:17'),
(451, 'Master of Social Work', 'Master of Social Work (Advanced Entry)', 'UFV\'s two-year Advanced Master of Social Work (MSW) equips you with the advanced practice knowledge and skills you need to move into a leadership role. The Advanced MSW program involves five-semesters, 30 credits and includes a required 450-hour practicum. The Advanced MSW program is offered every two years in even years.\r\n\r\nGraduates who do not have a Bachelor of Social Work can apply to our Foundational Master of Social Work program.\r\n\r\nUFV\'s three-year Foundational Master of Social Work (MSW) involves one-year of undergraduate social work courses, which involves three-semesters, 33 credits and a required 450-hour practicum.  Students will then ladder into the MSW program, which provides an advanced practice knowledge and the skills you need to move into a leadership role.  The MSW component of the program involves five-semesters, 30 credits and includes a required 450-hour practicum.  The Foundational program is also offered every two years in odd years.\r\n\r\nPlease note: the practicums in these programs (Foundational and Advanced) are not open to PLAR or challenge.\r\n\r\nUFV\'s Master of Social Work program builds on the success of UFV\'s Bachelor of Social Work program, and draws on the expertise of the School’s experienced and diverse faculty members. Strong relationships and consultation with community agencies in the Fraser Valley and Lower Mainland enhance the delivery of the MSW, particularly in terms of practicum placements and supervision.\r\n\r\nThe program is CASWE–ACFTS nationally accredited.', 1, 2, 82, '$12,960.00 CAD / Year', '2 Years', '4-Year Bachelor\'s Degree, Minimum GPA 73.0%,IELTS 6.5', '$19,290.00 CAD / Year', '$250.00 CAD', 'Sep 2024', 'https://admin.edumatric.com/uploads/coursedocument/vTZ8cur4wsT3j9GnCeiugtV2nE1K4SXjGrQP4HWQ.png', '2023-09-30 18:00:00', '2024-03-09 18:00:00', '2023-09-10 04:04:56', '2023-09-10 04:04:56');
